Utterances.UttText: A 54-year-old woman presented with giant struma, hyperthyroidism of unknown duration, palpitations and dyspnoea.
The ECG showed tachycardia atrial fibrillation.
Echocardiography revealed dilatation of the left ventricle, highly reduced systolic function and diffuse hypokinesia.

Serum thyroid stimulating hormone (TSH) levels were less than 0.03 lU/ml (physiological range 0.554.78 lU/ ml), free triiodothyronine (fT3) was 7.32 pg/ml (2.304.20 pg/ml) and free thyroxine (fT4) amounted to Fig.
